I can not post on this thread, as I was not there. But I can offer this, because of this site.  Today, I went to a Fry Electronics Store near Little Saigon. It is an ugly store the size of a warehouse. It was packed. At least half the shoppers were vietnamese, as were about a third of the employee's.  I had been there before and I left feeling angry and pissed off. Both with the story and its long documented rip off policies, but also having been thrust into and among so many non english speaking, asians.<br><br>
Today was different. Today was mellow. The story still sucks and rips you off at every turn. But I found that I was enjoying seeing Vietnamese. Talked to several in the aisle's about zip drives, and my check out guy, Mr. Nugyen, and I had several laughs about the store as he did my bill.  I saw him for the individual he was, not for his race.<br><br>
Thank you POV. This old dog keeps learning new tricks<br><br>
